[3
Date: Sat, 12 Jun 1999 07:49:12 -0800
From: Henry Wilde, MD <awilde@alaska.net>

England and Scotland experimented with anthrax during World War I. They
dumped some spores on an island north of Scotland which is still
uninhabited now, some 80 years later. Spores of anthrax survive virtually
indefinitely in soil. They do have problems in Uzbekistan. It is almost
like dealing with some nuclear waste.
--
Henry Wilde, MD
e-mail: awilde@alaska.net
